{"questionId":"9517","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Consider the system of paired differential equations</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\dot x = ax + by\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mover>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mo>˙</mo>\n    </mover>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>a</mi>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>b</mi>\n  <mi>y</mi>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\dot y = cx + dy\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mover>\n      <mi>y</mi>\n      <mo>˙</mo>\n    </mover>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>c</mi>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>d</mi>\n  <mi>y</mi>\n</math></span>.</p>\n<p>This system is going to be solved by using the eigenvalue method.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>If the system has a pair of purely imaginary eigenvalues</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find two conditions that must be satisfied by <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a\">\n  <mi>a</mi>\n</math></span>, <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"b\">\n  <mi>b</mi>\n</math></span>, <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"c\">\n  <mi>c</mi>\n</math></span>, <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"d\">\n  <mi>d</mi>\n</math></span>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>Using the working from part (a) (or using the characteristic equation) for a pair of purely imaginary eigenvalues require</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a + d = 0\">\n  <mi>a</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>d</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span> and&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\left( {a - d} \\right)^2} + 4bc < 0\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mi>a</mi>\n          <mo>−</mo>\n          <mi>d</mi>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>4</mn>\n  <mi>b</mi>\n  <mi>c</mi>\n  <mo>&lt;</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp;R1A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" \\Rightarrow d =&nbsp; - a\">\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">⇒</mo>\n  <mi>d</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mi>a</mi>\n</math></span> and&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" \\Rightarrow {a^2} + bc < 0\">\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">⇒</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>a</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>b</mi>\n  <mi>c</mi>\n  <mo>&lt;</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp;A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[5 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9517","referenceCode":"EXM.3.AHL.TZ0.1b.i","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find two conditions that must be satisfied by a , b , c , d .","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 5]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","AHL 5.17—Phase portrait"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}